Control Data Corp., Minneapolis, said it has completed the previously announced sale of certain businesses in its Training and Education Group.
Terms weren't disclosed. 

The company sold Control Data Institutes, which are vocational training schools, and the Institute for Advanced Technology seminar business, to Human Capital Corp., Minneapolis.
Control Data said its Training and Education business was sold to a new company formed by William R. Roach & Associates of Chicago.
Control Data said it will retain a 20% stake in the new company, expected to have initial annual revenue of about $50 million. 

The company said it will retain full ownership of its industrial, higher education, and government training businesses.
It has said it would sell the schools as part of a restructuring plan to focus on its computer services and systems integration markets. 

